          </div>
          <div class="case-result">
            <div class="result-kpi">
              <span class="kpi-val">+90%</span>
              <span class="kpi-label">Stability improvement</span>
            </div>
            <div class="result-kpi">
              <span class="kpi-val">72hr</span>
              <span class="kpi-label">Zero-anomaly stress test</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="case-card">
          <div class="case-tag">Large-Scale Deployment</div>
          <h3 class="case-title">Batch Maintenance — 1,000-Server GPU Cluster</h3>
          <div class="case-meta">
            <span>Scale: ~10,000 GPU cards</span>
            <span>Resident engineers: 2</span>
            <span>Contract: Long-term</span>
          </div>
          <p>A hyperscale operator's GPU cluster had a 10% device failure rate creating security risks. Vertex Services deployed resident O&M engineers, provided seasonal inspection, fault-order analysis, on-site part replacement, and comprehensive training for the customer's own team.</p>
          <div class="case-faults">
            <div class="case-fault"><strong>Training delivered:</strong> GPU architecture, fault localisation, disassembly/assembly, hardware identification, and behavioural deviation correction.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="case-result">
            <div class="result-kpi">
              <span class="kpi-val">10% → 3%</span>
              <span class="kpi-label">Fault rate reduction</span>
            </div>
            <div class="result-kpi">
              <span class="kpi-val">&lt;8hr</span>
              <span class="kpi-label">Non-cluster interruptions</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="case-card">
          <div class="case-tag">H8XX SXM5 GPU</div>
          <h3 class="case-title">VRAM Chip Replacement — Data Centre Efficiency Recovery</h3>
          <div class="case-meta">
            <span>Response: 30 min</span>
            <span>On-site: 6 hrs</span>
            <span>Cause: Voltage spike</span>
          </div>
          <p>Damage to an H8XX module caused a sharp decline in data-processing efficiency. Error log analysis and initial data checks pointed to a VRAM chip abnormality. Specialised inspection confirmed a core component fault caused by voltage fluctuation.</p>
